          <!-- Style system -->
          <div class="doc-section" id="style-system">
            <h2>Style system</h2>
            <p>Prism illustrations must visually align with Zoho Puvi typography, 1.5px icon strokes, rounded interface corners, semantic color tokens, and dark mode surfaces.</p>

            <h3>Style rules</h3>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Rounded geometric shapes</li>
              <li>Clean enterprise-friendly metaphors</li>
              <li>Minimal scene depth</li>
              <li>Clear foreground focus</li>
              <li>Neutral supporting objects</li>
              <li>Optional semantic accent colors</li>
              <li>Dark-mode-safe surfaces</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Never mix illustration styles across modules.</p>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider">

          <!-- Accessibility -->
          <div class="doc-section" id="accessibility">
            <h2>Accessibility</h2>
            <p>Illustrations must never carry critical meaning alone.</p>
            <h3>Rules</h3>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Always pair with text</li>
              <li>Decorative visuals must use <code style="font-size:13px; background:var(--prism-surface); padding:3px 8px; border-radius:6px; color:var(--prism-violet-light); border:1px solid var(--prism-border);">aria-hidden</code></li>
              <li>Informative visuals require alt text</li>
              <li>Preserve contrast in dark mode</li>
              <li>Avoid flashing success animations</li>
              <li>Do not embed text inside illustration art</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Illustrations support clarity, not accessibility bypass.</p>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider">

          <!-- Anti-patterns -->
          <div class="doc-section" id="anti-patterns">
            <h2>Anti-patterns</h2>
            <p>Avoid these common enterprise UX failures:</p>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Decorative threat illustrations in dense dashboards</li>
              <li>Screenshot-style UI inside onboarding</li>
              <li>Different illustration styles per module</li>
              <li>AI-only purple magic graphics</li>
              <li>Overly playful malware scenes</li>
              <li>Dense background patterns behind tables</li>
              <li>Large illustrations inside confirmation modals</li>
              <li>Using illustration instead of clear CTA text</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider">

          <!-- Principle -->
          <div class="doc-section" id="principle">
            <h2>Principle</h2>
            <div class="principle-card">
              <p>In Prism, illustrations reduce uncertainty.</p>
              <p>The right illustration system helps admins <strong>understand workflows faster</strong>, <strong>recover confidently</strong>, and <strong>trust complex endpoint actions</strong>.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

